		<item>
		<title>Featured game: Word Cook</title>
		<link>/blog/2017/10/25/featured-game-word-cook/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 25 Oct 2017 17:40:47 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Rob Miracle]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Featured App]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">/?p=72941</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Check out this great #MadeWithCorona game from IcySpark - Word Cook!]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Word games are a popular genre which is a strong suit for games <a href=https://twitter.com/search?q=%23madewithcorona target="_blank" rel="noopener">#MadeWithCorona</a>. A great example is <a href=http://icyspark.com/wordcook/ target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Word Cook</em></a> from <strong>Dean Hodge</strong>, or you may know him better as <a href=http://icyspark.com/ target="_blank" rel="noopener"><strong>IcySpark</strong></a>. Based on a cooking theme, you take a series of letters and see how many words you can make with them.</p>
<div class="video-responsive"><iframe width="auto" height="auto" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/rSjMUE7WpSg?rel=0&amp;showinfo=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></div>
<p>Word Cook contains over 1,000 levels to stimulate your brain as you progress up the culinary ladder with increasingly difficult puzzles. The game contains impressive graphics and animations that are common with many of today&#8217;s high caliber games. It also features hints and the ability to ask friends for help.</p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-72944" src="/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/ss01-1024x512.png" alt="" width="1024" height="512" srcset="/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/ss01-1024x512.png 1024w, /wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/ss01-300x150.png 300w, /wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/ss01-768x384.png 768w, /wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/ss01-1000x500.png 1000w, /wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/ss01-700x350.png 700w, /wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/ss01-125x63.png 125w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></p>
<p>Word Cook is available on both the <a href=https://itunes.apple.com/app/id1187713193 target="_blank" rel="noopener">Apple App Store</a> and <a href=https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.icyspark.wordcook&rdid=com.icyspark.wordcook target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Play</a> as a free app with in-app purchases.</p>
<p><a href=https://itunes.apple.com/app/id1187713193 target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img class="alignnone wp-image-72086 size-full" src="/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/App-Store-Icon_200x200_badge.png" alt="" width="50" height="50" srcset="/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/App-Store-Icon_200x200_badge.png 200w, /wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/App-Store-Icon_200x200_badge-150x150.png 150w" sizes="(max-width: 50px) 100vw, 50px" /></a> <a href=https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.icyspark.wordcook&rdid=com.icyspark.wordcook target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-72174" src="/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/google-play-badge.png" alt="" width="50" height="50" srcset="/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/google-play-badge.png 200w, /wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/google-play-badge-150x150.png 150w" sizes="(max-width: 50px) 100vw, 50px" /></a></p>
]]></content:encoded>
