		<item>
		<title>Featured Game &#8211; Code Adventures</title>
		<link>/blog/2017/09/13/featured-game-code-adventures/</link>
		<pubDate>Wed, 13 Sep 2017 17:33:11 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Rob Miracle]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Featured App]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">/?p=72846</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[This week we introduce a great educational game where children can solve brain-challenging puzzles to learn basic programming techniques.]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><em>Code Adventures: Coding Puzzles For Kids</em> by Daniel Ivanov is a great educational game where children can solve brain-challenging puzzles to learn basic programming techniques. The goal is to help Aurora, a cute little fuzzball that is lost, find a way to get home.</p>
<div></div>
<div class="video-responsive"><iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/COt8UJkN8EU?rel=0&amp;showinfo=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></div>
<div></div>
<p>The game consists of 30 levels, some with single goals, others with multiple, that will require children to use logic and creative skills to complete. It also includes plenty of hints to keep players from becoming stuck.</p>
<p><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-72847" src="/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/codingadventuresss-1024x576.jpg" alt="" width="1024" height="576" srcset="/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/codingadventuresss-1024x576.jpg 1024w, /wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/codingadventuresss-300x169.jpg 300w, /wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/codingadventuresss-768x432.jpg 768w, /wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/codingadventuresss-700x394.jpg 700w, /wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/codingadventuresss-539x303.jpg 539w, /wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/codingadventuresss.jpg 1600w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></p>
<p><em>Code Adventures: Coding Puzzles For Kids</em> has been featured in over 150 countries in the <em>Educational and Puzzle Games</em> category and it made it to the feature banner on the home page in Russia. It&#8217;s available on the <a href=https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/code-adventures-programming-game-for-kids/id1184995400?mt=8 target="_blank" rel="noopener">Apple App Store</a>, <a href=https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.cyborc.codeadventures target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Play</a>, and <a href=https://www.amazon.com/gp/mas/dl/android?p=com.cyborc.codeadventures target="_blank" rel="noopener">Amazon Appstore</a> for $3.99.</p>
<p><a href=https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/code-adventures-programming-game-for-kids/id1184995400?mt=8 target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-72086" style="margin-right: 10px;" src="/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/App-Store-Icon_200x200_badge.png" alt="" width="50" height="50" srcset="/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/App-Store-Icon_200x200_badge.png 200w, /wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/App-Store-Icon_200x200_badge-150x150.png 150w" sizes="(max-width: 50px) 100vw, 50px" /></a> <a href=https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.cyborc.codeadventures target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-72174" style="margin-right: 10px;" src="/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/google-play-badge.png" alt="" width="50" height="50" srcset="/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/google-play-badge.png 200w, /wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/google-play-badge-150x150.png 150w" sizes="(max-width: 50px) 100vw, 50px" /></a> <a href=https://www.amazon.com/gp/mas/dl/android?p=com.cyborc.codeadventures target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-72087" src="/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/amazon-icon-badge-large-200.png" alt="" width="50" height="50" srcset="/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/amazon-icon-badge-large-200.png 200w, /wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/amazon-icon-badge-large-200-150x150.png 150w" sizes="(max-width: 50px) 100vw, 50px" /></a></p>
]]></content:encoded>
